PATCH: Update application report generation and minor fixes
Adjusted the report generation functions to retrieve data from the previous month instead of the current month. Fixed minor issues around login token retrieval, partial payment labeling, and report pagination. Additionally, updated some terms in the application UI for clarity.

Add recovery_token and expiration to PasswordRecovery model
Incorporated AsSource trait in PasswordRecovery model and replaced 'token' field with 'recovery_token'. Added 'recovery_expiration' field to manage recovery token validity. Updated DeleteInvalidatedTokens command to remove expired recovery tokens. Corresponding database migration is also included.

Add recovery_token and expiration to PasswordRecovery model
Incorporated AsSource trait in PasswordRecovery model and replaced 'token' field with 'recovery_token'. Added 'recovery_expiration' field to manage recovery token validity. Updated DeleteInvalidatedTokens command to remove expired recovery tokens. Corresponding database migration is also included.

Update CSRF token verification list
The CSRF token verification list has been updated to include new paths like '/request-new-password', 'switch-logout', and 'logout'. This safeguards these paths from cross-site request forgery attacks and enhances the overall security of the application.

Update action route in password recovery form
The action route in the password recovery form has been changed to 'login.recoveryChallengePost'. This change direct the request towards the correct recovery method and improves the password recovery process. This adjustment contributes to overall code efficiency and maintainability.
